casebody.data:
Frederick A. Stokes v. Nathaniel P. Jacobs. Assignments of error are not necessary on common law cerfcioraris. Decided June 3d. Certiorari to a Circuit Court Commissioner, to review his proceedings on the dissolution of an attachment. A. Russell, for plaintiff in error,

moved for leave to amend the assignment of errors; but

The Court

held that it was unnecessary, as no assignment of errors is required on a common law certiorari.
